  "body": " General   Rounding in calculations  Roundoff errors made at intermediate steps of a multi-step calculation tend to become magnified. For this reason, do not round off numbers until the final step of a calculation, unless you are simply making a rough estimate. If you must round, keep lots of digits. A rule of thumb is to round to the nearest , that is, to the nearest 3rd digit to the right of the decimal point.    Solving equations  To solve a given equation for a particular quantity means to manipulate the given equation into a new equation where is all by itself on one side. For example, the equation can be solved for by dividing both sides of the equation by (this is valid as long as is not zero). This manipulation results in the new equation which is solved for .  To solve the equation for , first multiply both sides of the equation by to obtain then add to both sides to obtain    Solving equations practice problems  Consider the equation . Solve for .  Solve for .  Solve for .             "
